{
  "texts": [
    "The reason she avoided buying a head-mounted eye tracker, for instance a pair of glasses, was that she aimed for computer screen-based research, where it seemed more reliable and easier to synchronize the eye tracking data to the visual stimulus presentation using a remote eye tracker.",
    "Ingrid thinks using a standard web camera with open-source software may also be sufficient for her research (e.g., Petridis et al., 2013; Wisiecka et al., 2022).",
    "However, it should be noted that changes in pupil diameter may not be accurately estimated by current web cameras, as many of them do not use infrared light, which makes it easier to separate the pupil from the background in the captured images (Kaduk et al., 2024).",
    "Depending on the type of analysis Ingrid wants to conduct, particular attention should be placed on the pre-processing of the pupil size data (Kret & Sjak-Shie, 2019).",
    "Kim is interested in whether people with a university degree read differently than people without a university degree, and how reading changes with age (elderly vs. adolescents)."
  ]
}